  Exercise 5
Decimal to hexadecimal conversion
How do you convert following decimal numbers into hexadecimal numbers?

1.548 
548 / 16 = 34 rem = 4
34 / 16 = 2   rem = 2
2 / 16  = 0   rem = 2
Ans = (548)10 = (224)8

2. 4052
4052 / 16 = 253 rem = 4
253 / 16  = 15 rem = 13
15 / 16 = 0    rem = 15
Ans = (4052)10 = (FD4)16

3.58 
58 / 16 = 3 rem = 10
3 / 16 = 0  rem = 3
Ans = (58)10 = (3A)16

Exercise 6
Binary to octal and hexadecimal conversion
How do you convert the following binary numbers into octal and hexadecimal numbers?

1.(1110001000)2

(1 110 001 000)2

1 110 001 000 = (1 6 1 0)8

(1110001000)2 = (1610)8

(1110 0010 0000)2

1110 0010 0000 = (E 2 0)16
Ans (111000100000)2 = (E20)16

2.(110110101)2

(1 101 101 01)2

1 101 101 01 = (1551)8

Ans (110110101)2 = (1551)8

(1101 1010 1001) = (D A 9)16

(110110101001) = (DA9)16

3.(1010100)2

1 010 100 = (1 2 4)8

(1010100)2 = (124)8

(1010 1000)2

1010 1000 = (A 8)16
(10101000)2 = (A8)16


